Mikel Arteta is targeting Napoli centre-half Kalidou Koulibaly as his first signing as Arsenal manager, according to Reach PLC’s Transfer Window Podcast. “I’ve heard, although can’t confirm, that Arsenal have also made contact with Napoli through a third-party regarding Koulibaly,” said host Ian McGarry. “This comes on the back of their desire under Mikel Arteta to strengthen their defence.”